{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Forget","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Preserves.Shapes.Products","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.SheafCondition.EqualizerProducts"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.lean#L163-L232","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheaf_comp","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.html#TopCat.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheaf_comp","doc":"If `G : C ⥤ D` is a functor which reflects isomorphisms and preserves limits\n(we assume all limits exist in both `C` and `D`),\nthen checking the sheaf condition for a presheaf `F : presheaf C X`\nis equivalent to checking the sheaf condition for `F ⋙ G`.\n\nThe important special case is when\n`C` is a concrete category with a forgetful functor\nthat preserves limits and reflects isomorphisms.\nThen to check the sheaf condition it suffices to check it on the underlying sheaf of types.\n\nAnother useful example is the forgetful functor `TopCommRing ⥤ Top`.\n\nSee <https://stacks.math.columbia.edu/tag/0073>.\nIn fact we prove a stronger version with arbitrary complete target category.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.lean#L106-L128","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.SheafCondition.mapConeFork","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.html#TopCat.Presheaf.SheafCondition.mapConeFork","doc":"When `G` preserves limits, the image under `G` of the sheaf condition fork for `F`\nis the sheaf condition fork for `F ⋙ G`,\npostcomposed with the inverse of the natural isomorphism `diagramCompPreservesLimits`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.lean#L69-L96","name":"TopCat.Presheaf.SheafCondition.diagramCompPreservesLimits","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Forget.html#TopCat.Presheaf.SheafCondition.diagramCompPreservesLimits","doc":"When `G` preserves limits, the sheaf condition diagram for `F` composed with `G` is\nnaturally isomorphic to the sheaf condition diagram for `F ⋙ G`.\n"}]}